27/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski has officially set 13 March as the date for the next local elections. 
The chairman of the State Election Commission, Stevo Pendarovski, said Sunday (26 December) that the vote would be held in line with the new law on territorial organisation and the country's administrative division into 85 municipalities.
The ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM) has already started preparations for the vote. 
Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski confirmed that talks on expanding SDSM's For Macedonia Together coalition are under way. 
In an interview with the Macedonian Radio broadcast Saturday, he vowed to boost the fight against corruption in the coming months. 
(Dnevnik, Macedonian government Web site - 27/12/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 26/12/04)
